# Code Conventions

## General

- Use TypeScript with strict typing.
- Prefer named exports by default.
- Prefer `@/` imports for app source code.
- Keep files focused and avoid mixing unrelated responsibilities.
- Follow existing naming patterns already present in the repo.

## React Native and Expo Router

- Keep `app/` files route-oriented and thin.
- Move substantial UI and feature logic into `src/features`.
- Avoid embedding business rules directly in route components.
- Prefer extracting repeated UI into `src/components` only when truly shared.

## State and Logic

- App-level stores belong in `src/appState`.
- Business rules belong in `src/domain`.
- Integration logic belongs in `src/services`.
- Shared hooks belong in `src/hooks`.
- Pure helpers belong in `src/utils`.

## Styling and Theme

- Reuse tokens from `src/theme` before introducing new colors, typography, or strings.
- Avoid repeated hardcoded literals when a shared token is appropriate.
- Keep visual decisions consistent with existing app background and dark presentation patterns.

## Changes to Avoid

- Do not make architecture changes casually from a local UI edit.
- Do not move files across ownership areas unless the task explicitly requires it.
- Do not modify backend contracts, store shape, or domain rules from a UI-only task without clear instruction.

## Testing

- Add or update tests when changing behavior in `src/domain`, `src/services`, `src/utils`, paywall logic, subscription logic, or AI behavior.
- Prefer focused regression coverage for changed logic instead of broad snapshots.
